<section style="max-width: 62ch;">
  <div class="tb-eyebrow">About</div>
  <h1 class="tb-h1 tb-tool-title">An honest workshop.</h1>

  <div class="tb-text" style="margin-top: 20px;">
    <p>
      Arolel is a set of small web utilities, held together by one promise: we do not want your files,
      your email, or your money. If a tool saves you a few minutes, you can
      <a href="<%= ENV.fetch("COFFEE_URL", "https://buymeacoffee.com/arolel") %>" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color: var(--tb-red); text-decoration: underline;">buy us a coffee</a>.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top: 14px;">
      Most file tools run entirely in your browser — there is no upload step. A compact live receipt
      at the top of those pages reads your browser's own resource timing API and tells you, in real time,
      exactly how many bytes and requests this page has sent to our origin since you arrived.
      Document conversions use temporary server uploads only when LibreOffice or Poppler is required.
    </p>
    <p style="margin-top: 14px;">
      Is It Down? and Bulk URL opener are only useful if they are shareable, so they live on our small Rails server.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
